name: datastore
title: Google Cloud Datastore API
description: Accesses the schemaless NoSQL database to provide fully managed, robust, scalable storage for your application.

parameters.name: prettyPrint
parameters.desc: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

parameters.name: key
parameters.desc: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

parameters.name: fields
parameters.desc: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

parameters.name: oauth_token
parameters.desc: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

parameters.name: quotaUser
parameters.desc: Available to use for quota purposes for server-side applications. Can be any arbitrary string assigned to a user, but should not exceed 40 characters.

schemas.name: PathElement
schemas.desc:
A (kind, ID/name) pair used to construct a key path.

If either name or ID is set, the element is complete.
If neither is set, the element is incomplete.

fields.name: id
fields.desc:
The auto-allocated ID of the entity.
Never equal to zero. Values less than zero are discouraged and may not
be supported in the future.

fields.name: name
fields.desc:
The name of the entity.
A name matching regex `__.*__` is reserved/read-only.
A name must not be more than 1500 bytes when UTF-8 encoded.
Cannot be `""`.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc:
The kind of the entity.
A kind matching regex `__.*__` is reserved/read-only.
A kind must not contain more than 1500 bytes when UTF-8 encoded.
Cannot be `""`.

schemas.name: RollbackResponse
schemas.desc:
The response for Datastore.Rollback.
(an empty message).

schemas.name: Key
schemas.desc:
A unique identifier for an entity.
If a key's partition ID or any of its path kinds or names are
reserved/read-only, the key is reserved/read-only.
A reserved/read-only key is forbidden in certain documented contexts.

fields.name: partitionId
fields.desc:
Entities are partitioned into subsets, currently identified by a project
ID and namespace ID.
Queries are scoped to a single partition.

fields.name: path
fields.desc:
The entity path.
An entity path consists of one or more elements composed of a kind and a
string or numerical identifier, which identify entities. The first
element identifies a _root entity_, the second element identifies
a _child_ of the root entity, the third element identifies a child of the
second entity, and so forth. The entities identified by all prefixes of
the path are called the element's _ancestors_.

An entity path is always fully complete: *all* of the entity's ancestors
are required to be in the path along with the entity identifier itself.
The only exception is that in some documented cases, the identifier in the
last path element (for the entity) itself may be omitted. For example,
the last path element of the key of `Mutation.insert` may have no
identifier.

A path can never be empty, and a path can have at most 100 elements.

schemas.name: LookupRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.Lookup.

fields.name: readOptions
fields.desc: The options for this lookup request.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc: Keys of entities to look up.

schemas.name: LatLng
schemas.desc: An object representing a latitude/longitude pair. This is expressed as a pair of doubles representing degrees latitude and degrees longitude. Unless specified otherwise, this must conform to the WGS84 standard. Values must be within normalized ranges. Example of normalization code in Python: def NormalizeLongitude(longitude): """Wraps decimal degrees longitude to [-180.0, 180.0].""" q, r = divmod(longitude, 360.0) if r > 180.0 or (r == 180.0 and q <= -1.0): return r - 360.0 return r def NormalizeLatLng(latitude, longitude): """Wraps decimal degrees latitude and longitude to [-90.0, 90.0] and [-180.0, 180.0], respectively.""" r = latitude % 360.0 if r <= 90.0: return r, NormalizeLongitude(longitude) elif r >= 270.0: return r - 360, NormalizeLongitude(longitude) else: return 180 - r, NormalizeLongitude(longitude + 180.0) assert 180.0 == NormalizeLongitude(180.0) assert -180.0 == NormalizeLongitude(-180.0) assert -179.0 == NormalizeLongitude(181.0) assert (0.0, 0.0) == NormalizeLatLng(360.0, 0.0) assert (0.0, 0.0) == NormalizeLatLng(-360.0, 0.0) assert (85.0, 180.0) == NormalizeLatLng(95.0, 0.0) assert (-85.0, -170.0) == NormalizeLatLng(-95.0, 10.0) assert (90.0, 10.0) == NormalizeLatLng(90.0, 10.0) assert (-90.0, -10.0) == NormalizeLatLng(-90.0, -10.0) assert (0.0, -170.0) == NormalizeLatLng(-180.0, 10.0) assert (0.0, -170.0) == NormalizeLatLng(180.0, 10.0) assert (-90.0, 10.0) == NormalizeLatLng(270.0, 10.0) assert (90.0, 10.0) == NormalizeLatLng(-270.0, 10.0) The code in logs/storage/validator/logs_validator_traits.cc treats this type as if it were annotated as ST_LOCATION.

fields.name: latitude
fields.desc: The latitude in degrees. It must be in the range [-90.0, +90.0].

fields.name: longitude
fields.desc: The longitude in degrees. It must be in the range [-180.0, +180.0].

schemas.name: PartitionId
schemas.desc:
A partition ID identifies a grouping of entities. The grouping is always
by project and namespace, however the namespace ID may be empty.

A partition ID contains several dimensions:
project ID and namespace ID.

Partition dimensions:

- May be `""`.
- Must be valid UTF-8 bytes.
- Must have values that match regex `[A-Za-z\d\.\-_]{1,100}`
If the value of any dimension matches regex `__.*__`, the partition is
reserved/read-only.
A reserved/read-only partition ID is forbidden in certain documented
contexts.

Foreign partition IDs (in which the project ID does
not match the context project ID ) are discouraged.
Reads and writes of foreign partition IDs may fail if the project is not in an active state.

fields.name: projectId
fields.desc: The ID of the project to which the entities belong.

fields.name: namespaceId
fields.desc: If not empty, the ID of the namespace to which the entities belong.

schemas.name: Projection
schemas.desc: A representation of a property in a projection.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to project.

schemas.name: RunQueryResponse
schemas.desc: The response for Datastore.RunQuery.

fields.name: batch
fields.desc: A batch of query results (always present).

fields.name: query
fields.desc: The parsed form of the `GqlQuery` from the request, if it was set.

schemas.name: QueryResultBatch
schemas.desc: A batch of results produced by a query.

fields.name: endCursor
fields.desc: A cursor that points to the position after the last result in the batch.

fields.name: skippedCursor
fields.desc:
A cursor that points to the position after the last skipped result.
Will be set when `skipped_results` != 0.

fields.name: entityResultType
fields.desc: The result type for every entity in `entity_results`.

enum.name: RESULT_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value is never used.

enum.name: PROJECTION
enum.desc: A projected subset of properties. The entity may have no key.

fields.name: moreResults
fields.desc: The state of the query after the current batch.

enum.name: MORE_RESULTS_TYPE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value is never used.

enum.name: NOT_FINISHED
enum.desc: There may be additional batches to fetch from this query.

enum.name: MORE_RESULTS_AFTER_LIMIT
enum.desc: The query is finished, but there may be more results after the limit.

enum.name: MORE_RESULTS_AFTER_CURSOR
enum.desc:
The query is finished, but there may be more results after the end
cursor.

fields.name: entityResults
fields.desc: The results for this batch.

fields.name: skippedResults
fields.desc: The number of results skipped, typically because of an offset.

fields.name: snapshotVersion
fields.desc:
The version number of the snapshot this batch was returned from.
This applies to the range of results from the query's `start_cursor` (or
the beginning of the query if no cursor was given) to this batch's
`end_cursor` (not the query's `end_cursor`).

In a single transaction, subsequent query result batches for the same query
can have a greater snapshot version number. Each batch's snapshot version
is valid for all preceding batches.
The value will be zero for eventually consistent queries.

schemas.name: MutationResult
schemas.desc: The result of applying a mutation.

fields.name: version
fields.desc:
The version of the entity on the server after processing the mutation. If
the mutation doesn't change anything on the server, then the version will
be the version of the current entity or, if no entity is present, a version
that is strictly greater than the version of any previous entity and less
than the version of any possible future entity.

fields.name: conflictDetected
fields.desc:
Whether a conflict was detected for this mutation. Always false when a
conflict detection strategy field is not set in the mutation.

fields.name: key
fields.desc:
The automatically allocated key.
Set only when the mutation allocated a key.

schemas.name: AllocateIdsResponse
schemas.desc: The response for Datastore.AllocateIds.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc:
The keys specified in the request (in the same order), each with
its key path completed with a newly allocated ID.

schemas.name: Value
schemas.desc:
A message that can hold any of the supported value types and associated
metadata.

fields.name: arrayValue
fields.desc:
An array value.
Cannot contain another array value.
A `Value` instance that sets field `array_value` must not set fields
`meaning` or `exclude_from_indexes`.

fields.name: doubleValue
fields.desc: A double value.

fields.name: geoPointValue
fields.desc: A geo point value representing a point on the surface of Earth.

fields.name: nullValue
fields.desc: A null value.

fields.name: blobValue
fields.desc:
A blob value.
May have at most 1,000,000 bytes.
When `exclude_from_indexes` is false, may have at most 1500 bytes.
In JSON requests, must be base64-encoded.

fields.name: booleanValue
fields.desc: A boolean value.

fields.name: keyValue
fields.desc: A key value.

fields.name: excludeFromIndexes
fields.desc:
If the value should be excluded from all indexes including those defined
explicitly.

fields.name: stringValue
fields.desc:
A UTF-8 encoded string value.
When `exclude_from_indexes` is false (it is indexed) , may have at most 1500 bytes.
Otherwise, may be set to at least 1,000,000 bytes.

fields.name: entityValue
fields.desc:
An entity value.

- May have no key.
- May have a key with an incomplete key path.
- May have a reserved/read-only key.

fields.name: meaning
fields.desc: The `meaning` field should only be populated for backwards compatibility.

fields.name: integerValue
fields.desc: An integer value.

fields.name: timestampValue

schemas.name: PropertyOrder
schemas.desc: The desired order for a specific property.

fields.name: direction
fields.desc: The direction to order by. Defaults to `ASCENDING`.

enum.name: DIRECTION_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value must not be used.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to order by.

schemas.name: Query
schemas.desc: A query for entities.

fields.name: limit
fields.desc:
The maximum number of results to return. Applies after all other
constraints. Optional.
Unspecified is interpreted as no limit.
Must be >= 0 if specified.

fields.name: offset
fields.desc:
The number of results to skip. Applies before limit, but after all other
constraints. Optional. Must be >= 0 if specified.

fields.name: projection
fields.desc: The projection to return. Defaults to returning all properties.

fields.name: kind
fields.desc:
The kinds to query (if empty, returns entities of all kinds).
Currently at most 1 kind may be specified.

fields.name: filter
fields.desc: The filter to apply.

fields.name: endCursor
fields.desc:
An ending point for the query results. Query cursors are
returned in query result batches and
[can only be used to limit the same query](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/docs/concepts/queries#cursors_limits_and_offsets).

fields.name: distinctOn
fields.desc:
The properties to make distinct. The query results will contain the first
result for each distinct combination of values for the given properties
(if empty, all results are returned).

fields.name: order
fields.desc: The order to apply to the query results (if empty, order is unspecified).

fields.name: startCursor
fields.desc:
A starting point for the query results. Query cursors are
returned in query result batches and
[can only be used to continue the same query](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/docs/concepts/queries#cursors_limits_and_offsets).

schemas.name: Filter
schemas.desc: A holder for any type of filter.

fields.name: propertyFilter
fields.desc: A filter on a property.

fields.name: compositeFilter
fields.desc: A composite filter.

schemas.name: BeginTransactionResponse
schemas.desc: The response for Datastore.BeginTransaction.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc: The transaction identifier (always present).

schemas.name: Mutation
schemas.desc: A mutation to apply to an entity.

fields.name: insert
fields.desc:
The entity to insert. The entity must not already exist.
The entity key's final path element may be incomplete.

fields.name: update
fields.desc:
The entity to update. The entity must already exist.
Must have a complete key path.

fields.name: baseVersion
fields.desc:
The version of the entity that this mutation is being applied to. If this
does not match the current version on the server, the mutation conflicts.

fields.name: upsert
fields.desc:
The entity to upsert. The entity may or may not already exist.
The entity key's final path element may be incomplete.

fields.name: delete
fields.desc:
The key of the entity to delete. The entity may or may not already exist.
Must have a complete key path and must not be reserved/read-only.

schemas.name: AllocateIdsRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.AllocateIds.

fields.name: keys
fields.desc:
A list of keys with incomplete key paths for which to allocate IDs.
No key may be reserved/read-only.

schemas.name: PropertyFilter
schemas.desc: A filter on a specific property.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: The value to compare the property to.

fields.name: op
fields.desc: The operator to filter by.

enum.name: OPERATOR_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value must not be used.

fields.name: property
fields.desc: The property to filter by.

schemas.name: ReadOptions
schemas.desc: The options shared by read requests.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc:
The identifier of the transaction in which to read. A
transaction identifier is returned by a call to
Datastore.BeginTransaction.

fields.name: readConsistency
fields.desc:
The non-transactional read consistency to use.
Cannot be set to `STRONG` for global queries.

enum.name: READ_CONSISTENCY_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value must not be used.

schemas.name: KindExpression
schemas.desc: A representation of a kind.

fields.name: name
fields.desc: The name of the kind.

schemas.name: LookupResponse
schemas.desc: The response for Datastore.Lookup.

fields.name: found
fields.desc:
Entities found as `ResultType.FULL` entities. The order of results in this
field is undefined and has no relation to the order of the keys in the
input.

fields.name: missing
fields.desc:
Entities not found as `ResultType.KEY_ONLY` entities. The order of results
in this field is undefined and has no relation to the order of the keys
in the input.

fields.name: deferred
fields.desc:
A list of keys that were not looked up due to resource constraints. The
order of results in this field is undefined and has no relation to the
order of the keys in the input.

schemas.name: Entity
schemas.desc:
A Datastore data object.

An entity is limited to 1 megabyte when stored. That _roughly_
corresponds to a limit of 1 megabyte for the serialized form of this
message.

fields.name: properties
fields.desc:
The entity's properties.
The map's keys are property names.
A property name matching regex `__.*__` is reserved.
A reserved property name is forbidden in certain documented contexts.
The name must not contain more than 500 characters.
The name cannot be `""`.

fields.name: key
fields.desc:
The entity's key.

An entity must have a key, unless otherwise documented (for example,
an entity in `Value.entity_value` may have no key).
An entity's kind is its key path's last element's kind,
or null if it has no key.

schemas.name: CommitRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.Commit.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc:
The identifier of the transaction associated with the commit. A
transaction identifier is returned by a call to
Datastore.BeginTransaction.

fields.name: mode
fields.desc: The type of commit to perform. Defaults to `TRANSACTIONAL`.

enum.name: MODE_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value must not be used.

enum.name: TRANSACTIONAL
enum.desc:
Transactional: The mutations are either all applied, or none are applied.
Learn about transactions [here](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/docs/concepts/transactions).

enum.name: NON_TRANSACTIONAL
enum.desc: Non-transactional: The mutations may not apply as all or none.

fields.name: mutations
fields.desc:
The mutations to perform.

When mode is `TRANSACTIONAL`, mutations affecting a single entity are
applied in order. The following sequences of mutations affecting a single
entity are not permitted in a single `Commit` request:

- `insert` followed by `insert`
- `update` followed by `insert`
- `upsert` followed by `insert`
- `delete` followed by `update`

When mode is `NON_TRANSACTIONAL`, no two mutations may affect a single
entity.

schemas.name: RunQueryRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.RunQuery.

fields.name: gqlQuery
fields.desc: The GQL query to run.

fields.name: readOptions
fields.desc: The options for this query.

fields.name: query
fields.desc: The query to run.

fields.name: partitionId
fields.desc:
Entities are partitioned into subsets, identified by a partition ID.
Queries are scoped to a single partition.
This partition ID is normalized with the standard default context
partition ID.

schemas.name: EntityResult
schemas.desc: The result of fetching an entity from Datastore.

fields.name: cursor
fields.desc:
A cursor that points to the position after the result entity.
Set only when the `EntityResult` is part of a `QueryResultBatch` message.

fields.name: entity
fields.desc: The resulting entity.

fields.name: version
fields.desc:
The version of the entity, a strictly positive number that monotonically
increases with changes to the entity.

This field is set for `FULL` entity
results.

For missing entities in `LookupResponse`, this
is the version of the snapshot that was used to look up the entity, and it
is always set except for eventually consistent reads.

schemas.name: GqlQueryParameter
schemas.desc: A binding parameter for a GQL query.

fields.name: value
fields.desc: A value parameter.

fields.name: cursor
fields.desc:
A query cursor. Query cursors are returned in query
result batches.

schemas.name: ArrayValue
schemas.desc: An array value.

fields.name: values
fields.desc:
Values in the array.
The order of this array may not be preserved if it contains a mix of
indexed and unindexed values.

schemas.name: PropertyReference
schemas.desc: A reference to a property relative to the kind expressions.

fields.name: name
fields.desc:
The name of the property.
If name includes "."s, it may be interpreted as a property name path.

schemas.name: BeginTransactionRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.BeginTransaction.

schemas.name: RollbackRequest
schemas.desc: The request for Datastore.Rollback.

fields.name: transaction
fields.desc:
The transaction identifier, returned by a call to
Datastore.BeginTransaction.

schemas.name: GqlQuery
schemas.desc: A [GQL query](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/docs/apis/gql/gql_reference).

fields.name: queryString
fields.desc:
A string of the format described
[here](https://cloud.google.com/datastore/docs/apis/gql/gql_reference).

fields.name: namedBindings
fields.desc:
For each non-reserved named binding site in the query string, there must be
a named parameter with that name, but not necessarily the inverse.

Key must match regex `A-Za-z_$*`, must not match regex
`__.*__`, and must not be `""`.

fields.name: allowLiterals
fields.desc:
When false, the query string must not contain any literals and instead must
bind all values. For example,
`SELECT * FROM Kind WHERE a = 'string literal'` is not allowed, while
`SELECT * FROM Kind WHERE a = @value` is.

fields.name: positionalBindings
fields.desc:
Numbered binding site @1 references the first numbered parameter,
effectively using 1-based indexing, rather than the usual 0.

For each binding site numbered i in `query_string`, there must be an i-th
numbered parameter. The inverse must also be true.

schemas.name: CommitResponse
schemas.desc: The response for Datastore.Commit.

fields.name: mutationResults
fields.desc:
The result of performing the mutations.
The i-th mutation result corresponds to the i-th mutation in the request.

fields.name: indexUpdates
fields.desc:
The number of index entries updated during the commit, or zero if none were
updated.

schemas.name: CompositeFilter
schemas.desc: A filter that merges multiple other filters using the given operator.

fields.name: op
fields.desc: The operator for combining multiple filters.

enum.name: OPERATOR_UNSPECIFIED
enum.desc: Unspecified. This value must not be used.

enum.name: AND
enum.desc: The results are required to satisfy each of the combined filters.

fields.name: filters
fields.desc:
The list of filters to combine.
Must contain at least one filter.
